## DevFlo Dashboard MCP Tools

All user interactions and lifecycle tracking go through the DevFlo Dashboard via MCP tools.

### Asking Questions — `devflo_ask_user` (MANDATORY)

The ONLY acceptable method for asking user questions. Every agent (PM, Architect, Developer) must:

- Use `devflo_ask_user` with structured options for EVERY clarifying question
- NEVER present questions as inline markdown text in the response
- NEVER skip questions for New Feature or Major Refactor classifications
- Include 2–5 distinct options per question with trade-off descriptions and jargon-free explanations of technical terms/acronyms
- Include a "You decide — pick the best option" choice where appropriate
- Group related questions in a single `devflo_ask_user` call (pass multiple questions in the `questions` array)
- This is a blocker — do NOT proceed until the user answers via the dashboard

### Phase Tracking — `devflo_update_phase` (MANDATORY)

Call at every phase transition. Send only the **single phase** being updated — the server maintains the full phase list (seeded from the pipeline at `devflo_set_change_context`). When a phase becomes `active`, the server auto-completes the previously active phase (unless it has a pending gate). Params: `phaseName` (e.g. "Classification", "PM", "Developer"), `status` (pending|active|completed|skipped), `classification?`, `changeName?`, `confidence?`.

### Change Context — `devflo_set_change_context`

Call once after Phase 0. Seeds all 7 canonical phases (Classification, PM, Architect, Developer, QA, Test Summary, Cleanup) with skipped phases derived from the pipeline. Params: `name`, `classification`, `pipeline`, `workspacePath?`.

### Gate Approvals — `devflo_await_gate`

Call at Gate A/B instead of waiting for text input. Params: `gate` ("A"|"B"), `phaseName` ("PM"|"Architect"), `summary?`. Returns: `{ action: "approve"|"revise"|"cancel", feedback?: string }`. When `action` is `"revise"` and `feedback` is present, the user typed revision instructions in the dashboard — pass them directly to the agent in Revision mode. When `feedback` is absent, the user will type feedback in the Cursor chat instead.

### Task Board — `devflo_update_tasks`

Call when tasks are available and on status changes. Params: `tasks` (array of {id, title, status: pending|in_progress|completed|failed|cancelled, description?}).

### Activity Log — `devflo_log_event`

Call at key milestones. Params: `phase`, `agent` (pm|architect|dev|qa|orchestrator), `message`, `eventType` (info|success|warning|error).

### QA Results — `devflo_update_qa_results`

Call during Phase 4. Params: `verdict` (pass|fail|pending), `findings` (array of {id, severity: blocker|major|minor|nit, description, file?, line?, fixType?: surgical|structural}), `summary?`.

### Test Summary — `devflo_update_test_summary`

Call during Phase 5. Params: `commands`, `suites`, `total`, `passed`, `failed`, `skipped`, `integrationResult?`, `notes?`.

---

## Enforcement

**Must refuse to:**
- Write code before required approvals (per pipeline)
- Skip QA (except Trivial + explicit SKIP QA)
- Close without producing Test Summary
- Skip Phase 6 documentation updates
- Process SKIP QA for non-Trivial
- Pass a gate without explicit approval text

**Must NEVER:**
- Suggest switching to Plan, Ask, or any other mode. Always operate in Agent mode.
- Ask permission to proceed after a gate passes or phase completes. Phase transitions are automatic — only Gate A and Gate B are pause points.

---

## Confidence Signals

Every agent output must end with: **Confidence: HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW**

- **HIGH**: Clear inputs, no ambiguity, standard patterns
- **MEDIUM**: Some inference required, assumptions documented
- **LOW**: Significant ambiguity — must explain what drove it
